  <main>
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="hero-copy"><h1>Your team runs on telegram<br><span>Now run it like a system</span></h1><p>Turns your Telegram chaos into one clean control center.<br>Tracks every single ask, pending action, and daily number.<br>Zero migration required no new app to learn.</p><div class="hero-actions"><a class="button button-primary" href="/signup"><span aria-hidden="true">＋</span> Add tegsi to your group</a><a class="button button-light" href="#products">Request a demo <span aria-hidden="true">›</span></a></div></div>
    </section>
    <section class="gap-section section" id="why"><div class="section-heading"><span class="kicker">The Gap</span><h2>Telegram gives you the conversation it<br>gives you nothing to run the work</h2><p>Think of your groups as a plant floor with no instrumentation. Tegsi adds the three layers any control system needs, all sourced from chat your team already lives in.</p></div><div class="gap-grid"><article class="gap-card"><img src="/figma/gap-chat.png" alt=""><div><h3>Work disappears into chat</h3><p>An ask scrolls past, nobody owns it, and there’s no trace of what was promised or done.</p></div></article><article class="gap-card"><img src="/figma/gap-blue.png" alt=""><div><h3>No view across groups</h3><p>What’s stuck in sales, ops, support? Today the only way to find out is to ask—slow, then, every day.</p></div></article><article class="gap-card"><img src="/figma/gap-paper.png" alt=""><div><h3>Numbers copied by hand</h3><p>Someone scrapes today’s sales, leads and updates from the groups into a sheet—slow, late, and error-prone.</p></div></article></div></section>
    <section class="products-section section" id="products"><div class="products-intro"><span class="kicker">One control system, three instruments</span><h2>Commands. Alarms.<br>Instruments</h2><p>Think of your groups as a plant floor with no instrumentation. Tegsi adds the three layers any control system needs — all sourced from chat your team already lives in.</p></div><div class="product-stack"><article class="product-card"><header><div><h3>Can Anyone</h3><small>Turn any message into trackable work</small></div><span>Commands · Intake</span></header><div class="product-body"><p>Anyone posts an ask in the group. Anyone else can claim it, log effort, and mark it complete — right inside the chat.</p><ul><li>ask → claim → effort → complete</li><li>Clear ownership, no message lost</li><li>Mirrored to the web dashboard</li></ul></div></article><article class="product-card"><header><div><h3>Action Log</h3><small>Every pending item, every group, one screen</small></div><span>Alarms · State</span></header><div class="product-body"><p>Add the bot to your groups and Tegsi harvests every outstanding action into a single control view. Finally know what’s stuck — across the whole org.</p><ul><li>Cross-group, top-down oversight</li><li>Built for the founder / COO / ops lead</li><li>Value compounds with every group added</li></ul></div></article><article class="product-card"><header><div><h3>Signals</h3><small>Your daily numbers, pulled and reported</small></div><span>Instruments · Metrics</span></header><div class="product-body"><p>Define the data points you care about. Tegsi extracts them from chat on a schedule and reports them — with the source message one tap away.</p><ul><li>Scheduled daily report, automatic</li><li>Accumulates history → trends &amp; anomalies</li><li>Replaces the morning copy-paste job</li></ul></div></article></div></section>
    <section class="engine-section section" id="how"><div class="section-heading"><span class="kicker">How it works</span><h2>One engine reads your groups. Every<br>product gets smarter together.</h2><p>Under all three tools sits a single capability, a message understanding layer over your Telegram groups. Build it once, and intake, alarms and instruments all ride on it. That convergence is something Telegram won’t build and a generic bot can’t match.</p></div><div class="engine-flow"><article><b>01</b><div class="engine-icon people"></div><h3>Telegram groups</h3><p>where work already happens</p></article><article><b>02</b><div class="engine-icon layers"></div><h3>Tegsi engine</h3><p>classify · extract · structure</p></article><article><b>03</b><div class="engine-icon dashboard"></div><h3>Control dashboard</h3><p>work · pending · signals</p></article></div></section>
    <section class="audience-section section"><div class="section-heading"><span class="kicker">Who it’s for</span><h2>Adoption from the team. Value for the boss.</h2><p>Tegsi is loved by the people doing the work and paid for by the people who need to see it.</p></div><div class="audience-grid"><article><span>The doer</span><h3>Anyone in the group</h3><p>Drops an ask, claims a task, marks it done — without leaving Telegram. Zero new habits, zero new app. This is what drives adoption across the org.</p></article><article><span>The overseer</span><h3>Founder · COO · Ops lead</h3><p>Gets the one thing they don’t have today: visibility. What’s pending everywhere, what moved, and the daily numbers — in a control center that becomes part of the morning routine.</p></article></div></section>
